text: The Grand Union Canal in England is part of the British canal system. Its main line starts in London and ends in Birmingham. It is with 166 locks. It has arms to places including Leicester, Slough, Aylesbury, Wendover and Northampton. The Grand Union Canal was also the original name for what now generally referred to as the Old Grand Union Canal to avoid ambiguity. == References == Category:Geography of Northamptonshire Category:Geography of Warwickshire Category:Geography of Berkshire Category:Geography of Leicestershire Category:Geography of Buckinghamshire Category:Geography of Hertfordshire Category:Canals in England
